%N A397550 Decimal expansion of Integral_{0..1} Li_4(x)^2 dx, where Li_4 is the polylogarithm function.
%H A397550 Pedro Freitas, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1090/S0025-5718-05-01747-3">Integrals of polylogarithmic functions, recurrence relations, and associated Euler sums</a>, Math. Comput., Vol. 74, No. 251 (2005), pp. 1425-1440. See p. 1435, Table 3.
%H A397550 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Polylogarithm.html">Polylogarithm</a>.
%F A397550 Equals 70 - 30*zeta(2) - 30*zeta(3) + 23*zeta(4) - 6*zeta(5) - 4*zeta(2)*zeta(3) + 7*zeta(6)/2 + 2*zeta(3)^2 - 2*zeta(3)*zeta(4) + 7*zeta(8)/6 [Freitas, 2005].
%e A397550 0.3728990100509510890547771660818533037913174890552643213992325254...
%t A397550 RealDigits[70 - 30*Zeta[2] - 30*Zeta[3] + 23*Zeta[4] - 6*Zeta[5] - 4*Zeta[2]*Zeta[3] + 7*Zeta[6]/2 + 2*Zeta[3]^2 - 2*Zeta[3]*Zeta[4] + 7*Zeta[8]/6, 10, 110][[1]]
%t A397550 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397550 NIntegrate[PolyLog[4, x]^2, {x, 0, 1}, WorkingPrecision->110]
%o A397550 (PARI) 70 - 30*zeta(2) - 30*zeta(3) + 23*zeta(4) - 6*zeta(5) - 4*zeta(2)*zeta(3) + 7*zeta(6)/2 + 2*zeta(3)^2 - 2*zeta(3)*zeta(4) + 7*zeta(8)/6 \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jul 06 2026
